        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 3 at 1:39PM CDT until April 3 at 2:30PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Sevier County in southwestern Arkansas...
Central McCurtain County in southeastern Oklahoma...
Northeastern Red River County in northeastern Texas...

* Until 230 PM CDT.

* At 139 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles southwest
of Idabel, or 15 miles north of Clarksville, moving northeast at 45
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Eagletown, Broken Bow, Farmers Hill, Idabel, Hochatown, Millerton,
Negley, Mount Herman, Sherwood, Silver City, Wright City, Holly
Creek, Glover, Garvin, Albion, Bethel, Oak Hill, Bryarly, Golden,
and Haworth.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
